A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 13 of Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to general provisions regarding administrative procedure, so as to provide that the
3 "Georgia Administrative Procedure Act" shall apply to all executive branch agencies; to
4 provide for certain exceptions; to revise a definition; to provide for related matters; to repeal
5 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article 1 of Chapter 13 of Title 50 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
9 general provisions regarding administrative procedure, is amended by revising paragraph (1)
10 of Code Section 50-13-2, relating to definitions, as follows:
11 "(1) 'Agency' means, unless otherwise required by federal law, each state board, bureau,
12 commission, department, activity, or officer of the executive branch of state government
13 authorized by law expressly to make rules and regulations or to determine contested
14 cases, except. Such term shall specifically not include the General Assembly; or the
15 judiciary; the Governor; the State Board of Pardons and Paroles; the State Financing and
16 Investment Commission; the State Properties Commission; the Board of Bar Examiners;
